<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Blackpool have confirmed the signing of former Everton defender Luke Garbutt with a cheeky dig at Toffees boss Carlo Ancelotti.</p>

<p>Garbutt was released by Everton in June but when asked about the left-back's departure, Ancelotti admitted he didn't know who he was.</p>

<p>The 27-year-old joined Everton back in 2009 but only made 12 first team appearances for the club and had loan spells at seven different clubs.</p>

<p>Blackpool confirmed the signing of ex-Everton man Luke Garbutt with a cheeky social post</p>

<p>The club posted this pic of Carlo Ancelotti after he admitted he didn't know who Garbutt was</p>

<p>Garbutt left Everton in June after 11 years at the club but didn't feature under Ancelotti</p>

<p>Blackpool have now taken the opportunity to poke fun at Ancelotti's gaffe with a light-hearted post on Twitter shortly after confirming his arrival.</p>

<p>The tweet shows Ancelotti's confused face during a Zoom interview back in June which has gone down well with the club's supporters. </p>

<p>At the time, Garbutt saw the funny side of the Italian's error, tweeting: 'It's not his fault, it's the club's, however it's a belter tho!'</p>

<p>After announcing his arrival at Bloomfield Road, Garbutt revealed his desire to help the club return to the Championship.</p>

<p>He said; ' I'm pleased to be here at Blackpool and to get back playing football again. Me and the gaffer spoke last week and I really liked what he had to say.</p>

<p>'Hopefully we can push on and have a successful season.'</p>

<p>Blackpool have won one and lost one of their opening two League One games after finishing 13th last season. </p>
